                <h1>Should You List Every Job on Your Background Check?</h1>
                <p>When completing a background check, you aren't required to list every job you've held. Focus on relevant positions that showcase your experience and skills related to the job you're applying for. However, be honest about your work history, as discrepancies may raise concerns during the hiring process.</p>
